overview: The user initiated a request to significantly enhance the aesthetic
  appeal of their sleep questionnaire application. I began by conducting a
  detailed analysis of the existing visual design, identifying areas such as the
  generic color palette, plain backgrounds, and basic form elements as needing
  improvement. The approach involved implementing a new, calming sleep-themed
  color palette, redesigning core UI components like the progress bar,
  checkboxes, radio buttons, and sliders, and applying consistent, polished
  styling across all 14 sections of the questionnaire. This included a revamped
  intro section with feature cards and a more visually engaging report section.
  The goal was to transform the app from a generic template look to a
  professional, cohesive, and calming interface. During the final review, a
  console warning about a  value prop on an input was noted, which is a
  minor React debug message.
